  "prompt": "Does Google hire CS M. Techs from IISC and other IITs?",
  "response": "Yes, Google does hire Computer Science M.Tech graduates from institutions such as the Indian Institute of Science (IISc) and the Indian Institutes of Technology (IITs). These institutions are renowned for their rigorous academic curriculum and high standards, and graduates from these institutions are often considered highly proficient in their field.\n\nHiring processes at Google typically involve a series of interviews, including technical assessments and coding challenges, to evaluate the candidates' skills and knowledge. The company values talent and competence and recruits from top-tier institutions worldwide. If you are an M.Tech graduate from IISc or an IIT, ensure that you have a strong understanding of core computer science concepts and are well-prepared for the technical interviews to increase your chances of securing a position.",
